<subSubSection id="91F4650B2812FFBAFF1CF8FCFC4BFF4E" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="432" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" type="description">
<paragraph id="D95136802812FFBAFF1CF8FCFC4BFF4E" blockId="2.[151,1437,1827,2033]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,430]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="432" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">
Species in the Nearctic 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFE2AF8FCFE2FF8A7" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1899" box="[417,490,1827,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFE2AF8FCFE2FF8A7" box="[417,490,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">Bezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFE7AF8FCFD41F8A6" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[497,644,1827,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea" subGenus="Bezzia">
(
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFE71F8FCFDCEF8A7" box="[506,523,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">B</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFDA8F8FCFD41F8A6" box="[547,644,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex are most similar to and likely related to species in the 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFAD9F8FCFAA6F8A7" box="[1362,1379,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">B</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFAFAF8FCFF34F8FA" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="expolita" subGenus="Bezzia">
(
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFAF0F8FCFA49F8A7" box="[1403,1420,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">B</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFF1CF898FF34F8FA" box="[151,241,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">expolita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex. In articles by Wirth (1983), 
<bibRefCitation id="BD7F4B712812FFBBFD15F898FC6DF8FA" author="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Grogan, W. L. Jr." box="[670,936,1863,1889]" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" pagination="489 - 523" refId="ref33247" refString="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Grogan, W. L. Jr. (1983) The Nearctic species of the Bezzia bivittata group (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 96, 489 - 523." type="journal article" year="1983">Wirth &amp; Grogan (1983)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="BD7F4B712812FFBBFC55F898FB74F8FA" author="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Palchick, S. M. &amp; Forster, L." box="[990,1201,1863,1889]" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" pagination="155 - 175" refId="ref33386" refString="Wirth, W. W., Palchick, S. M. &amp; Forster, L. (1984) The North American predaceous midges of the Bezzia annulipes group (Dip- tera: Ceratopogonidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 86, 155 - 175." type="journal article" year="1984">
Wirth 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFBAEF898FB93F8FA" box="[1061,1110,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">et al</emphasis>
. (1984)
</bibRefCitation>
, their “Synoptic Key to Subgenera and Groups of Nearctic 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFDCDF8B4FD4AF81F" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1899" box="[582,655,1899,1924]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFDCDF8B4FD4AF81F" box="[582,655,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">Bezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” included three species groups in the “Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFB4FF8B4FAC8F81F" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1899" box="[1220,1293,1899,1924]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFB4FF8B4FAC8F81F" box="[1220,1293,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">Bezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F0A957E92812FFBBFA97F8B4FA83F81E" box="[1308,1350,1899,1925]" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" sensu="stricto">s. s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
”(
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFAD5F8B4FF1AF833" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">sensu stricto</emphasis>
), the 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFEA8F850FE45F832" box="[291,384,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">bivitatta</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFE1BF850FE19F832" baseAuthorityName="Winnertz" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[400,476,1935,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilis">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFE1BF850FE19F832" box="[400,476,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">nobilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFD9CF850FDB4F832" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[535,625,1935,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="expolita">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFD9CF850FDB4F832" box="[535,625,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">expolita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups. Their “ 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFCA3F850FC47F832" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[808,898,1935,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="expolita">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFCA3F850FC47F832" box="[808,898,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">expolita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group” includes all species in the 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFA9AF850FAAEF832" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1297,1387,1935,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="expolita">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFA9AF850FAAEF832" box="[1297,1387,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">expolita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFF1CF86CFF3DF856" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[151,248,1971,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFF1CF86CFF3DF856" box="[151,248,1971,1997]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complexes. Males in the 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFD96F86CFDB2F856" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[541,631,1971,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="expolita">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFD96F86CFDB2F856" box="[541,631,1971,1997]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">expolita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex differ from males in the 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032812FFBBFB8BF86CFBA4F856" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1024,1121,1971,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922812FFBBFB8BF86CFBA4F856" box="[1024,1121,1971,1997]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex in having slender, elongate to greatly elongate parameres, slender aedeagi and slender gonostyli that usually have pointed tips. Fe-males in the 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032813FFBAFEAFFF48FEBBFF2A" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[292,382,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="expolita">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFEAFFF48FEBBFF2A" box="[292,382,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">expolita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex differ from females in the 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032813FFBAFC9BFF48FCB4FF2A" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[784,881,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFC9BFF48FCB4FF2A" box="[784,881,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex by their usually non-banded femora and tibiae, and, their stout ovoid spermathecae are usually unequal-size.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91F4650B2813FFBAFF4CFF01FAF4FE35" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D95136802813FFBAFF4CFF01FAF4FE35" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFF4CFF01FE87FF63" bold="true" box="[199,322,222,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males in the 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFE69FF00FE36FF63" box="[482,499,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">B</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032813FFBAFD88FF00FD5DFF62" baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[515,664,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea" subGenus="Bezzia">
(
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFD87FF00FDD8FF63" box="[524,541,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">B</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFDBCFF00FD5DFF62" box="[567,664,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex are the only Nearctic species of 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFBF6FF00FB4BFF63" box="[1149,1166,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">B</emphasis>
. (
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032813FFBAFB2CFF00FB35FF63" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1899" box="[1191,1264,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFB2CFF00FB35FF63" box="[1191,1264,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">Bezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with broad to very broad aedeagi and parameres, and, most species have a slender to very short gonostylus with 1–2 apical prongs except for two species, 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032813FFBAFE29FEF8FDFEFEDA" authority="Grogan, 2020" authorityName="Grogan" authorityYear="2020" box="[418,571,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amblystyla" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFE29FEF8FE76FEDB" box="[418,435,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFE49FEF8FDFEFEDA" box="[450,571,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">amblystyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F0A957E92813FFBAFDC8FEF8FD45FEDA" box="[579,640,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032813FFBAFD33FEF8FCF1FEDA" authority="Grogan, 2020" authorityName="Grogan" authorityYear="2020" box="[696,820,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="folkertsi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFD33FEF8FD0CFEDB" box="[696,713,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFD53FEF8FCF1FEDA" box="[728,820,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">folkertsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F0A957E92813FFBAFCB7FEF8FCBEFEDA" box="[828,891,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which have a gonostylus with blunt or rounded apices that lack well developed apical prongs. Females are the only Nearctic species of 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFBF1FE94FB4EFEFF" box="[1146,1163,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">B</emphasis>
. (
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032813FFBAFB28FE94FB29FEFF" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1899" box="[1187,1260,331,356]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFB28FE94FB29FEFF" box="[1187,1260,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">Bezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with mediumsize to large, elongate, unequal-size spermathecae (larger 
<quantity id="1E169B652813FFBAFC9CFEB1FC7EFE12" box="[791,955,366,393]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="0.19" valueMax="0.25" valueMin="0.13">0.13–0.25 mm</quantity>
, smaller 
<quantity id="1E169B652813FFBAFB95FEB0FB04FE12" box="[1054,1217,367,393]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="0.125" valueMax="0.17" valueMin="0.08">0.08–0.17 mm</quantity>
long), except for 
<taxonomicName id="1EEE4D032813FFBAFA0FFEB0FF36FE36" authority="Grogan, 2020" authorityName="Grogan" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="folkertsi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFA0FFEB0FA50FE13" box="[1412,1429,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="EB9AEA922813FFBAFF1CFE4CFF36FE36" box="[151,243,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="432">folkertsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F0A957E92813FFBAFF71FE4CFEFDFE36" box="[250,312,403,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which has smaller, subequal-sized spermathecae (larger 
<quantity id="1E169B652813FFBAFC32FE4CFBDAFE36" box="[953,1055,403,429]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="0.09">0.09 mm</quantity>
, smaller 
<quantity id="1E169B652813FFBAFB0FFE4CFB2DFE36" box="[1156,1256,403,429]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="0.08">0.08 mm</quantity>
long).
